Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.24,0:04:04.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Honmaru became a Li'l Pants Wetter \Nafter just getting thrown by Jabao-san once?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.21,0:04:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,He really did!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.53,0:04:10.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Honmaru at any other age \Nwould still be Honmaru! {/honmaru was honmaru since long ago}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.25,0:04:13.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Honmaru! So you're just like me!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.25,0:04:16.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Hooray! Honmaru, Li'l Pants Wetter! {yeah, now I'm convinced it's an evolution of his nickname. Damn it. }
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.75,0:04:19.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Honmaru Li'l Pants Wetter!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.80,0:04:22.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Yay! Yay! The Great Pants Pisser! {oshikko dare?}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.76,0:04:26.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Me too! Me too! Me peed myself a lot, too! {unsure, yoku oneesan / ore sa chibiru?}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.26,0:04:29.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Me and Honmaru friends!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.53,0:04:36.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Iyona is watching, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.77,0:04:43.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Honmaru's inner Li'l Pants Wetter might get evoked again, \Nso better run away while you can.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.57,0:04:45.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Things will turn nasty if he does. {/because it's dirty/disgusting}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.07,0:04:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Honmaru! With magic, I can make everyone \Nwet their little pants with us! Everyone friends! {/become Li'l Pants wetters together}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.86,0:04:57.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Taru, I need you to just watch silently. \NWe need no magic today. {/watch silently, I'll do it w/o magic}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.67,0:04:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(0,150)} Jabao!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.79,0:05:02.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Be it sumo or whatnot, it won't frighten me! {/I can do anything, even sumo}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.31,0:05:06.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you look down on me as a Li'l Pants Wetter \Njust cause I lost to you in the past! {itsumademo teme ni makete mo ... to omowanai no yo - do you think I'll stay ... forever after losing to you}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.72,0:05:08.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Honmaru-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.21,0:05:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.10,0:05:16.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Say, I did it with even less effort than the last time. {hope it's omee in the beg.} {/you've become even weaker than before }
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.60,0:05:18.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn you...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.25,0:05:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Once again! {/one more}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.03,0:05:26.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Why can't I do a single thing to Jabao?! {unsure who he asks this but なんで 。。。に勝てない has to be it - why can't I win against jabao}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.86,0:05:26.91,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\c&H0A22AC&\3c&H03050A&\4c&H0CA3BB&\shad3\b1\blur0.6\bord1}Ouch! {痛こえ - sound of pain}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.99,0:05:27.03,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\c&H002A3A&\3c&H8BB8C1&\blur0.6\bord3}Potato Chips{no idea what's pokochi if it's ぽこち, would assume some irl snacks reference; TLC?} {Au: 5:26: This is actually ぽてち which is the japanese abbreviation of the english word "potato chips"\NThe fish are a reference to goldfish warning; a manga in serialization around same time as Taruruuto-kun.}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.11,0:05:27.16,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\c&H002A3A&\3c&H8BB8C1&\blur0.6\bord3}Potato Chips
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.03,0:05:28.07,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\c&H1935AB&\3c&H042C3F&\bord1.5\b1\blur0.6\shad2\4c&H49B29F&}Ugh!! {/eh!!}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.37,0:05:28.99,Default,,0,0,0,,It hurts!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.57,0:05:31.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(00,100)}What the hell?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.51,0:05:37.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Teacher...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.87,0:05:41.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Your class had started a long time ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.48,0:05:43.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't you hear the school bell? {/chime}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.47,0:05:48.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Why didn't you tell me before, Taru?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.61,0:05:51.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Taru!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.64,0:05:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Honmaru told me to watch silently!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.98,0:05:57.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I watched and kept silent.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.98,0:06:04.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Teacher, it was Honmaru who kept asking for it, \Nnotwithstanding the fact that he's such a weakling.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.73,0:06:06.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Who're you calling a weakling?! {/not weak}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.75,0:06:08.85,Default,,0,0,0,,How about you beat me before you say anything? {/what are you saying despite you can't defeat me} {/first to say something}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.41,0:06:12.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the only sport that fatasses are cut out for. {/only activity fat people can do}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.45,0:06:14.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Whaddya say!?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.33,0:06:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You heard me!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.98,0:06:17.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I get it!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.62,0:06:22.86,Default,,0,0,0,,For ten days, starting today \Nwe'll be doing sumo for PE class.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.86,0:06:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, on the last day, we'll hold a match \Nto find out who the strongest wrestler in the class is.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.52,0:06:28.59,Default,,0,0,0,,How about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.00,0:06:30.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it fine with everyone else, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.43,0:06:35.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Sumo...?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.75,0:06:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? What's the matter, Harako-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.38,0:06:39.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You're unusually quiet today.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.77,0:06:43.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Rightly said. \NHarako, what became of your usual enthusiasm?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.94,0:06:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Aren't{/weren't you} you some Junior Sumo World Champion Wrestler \Namong kindergarteners? {yokozuna (highest rank in sumo); grand champion}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.90,0:06:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Sumo doesn't fit my style.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.00,0:06:52.28,Default,,0,0,0,,If you just look at me, {/you can understand from the looks of it}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.97,0:06:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,it'll be clear as day: becoming a fatso \Njust for the sake of some sports is below me. {unsure what he means: "something like the peak/apex of an overweight child, is not worth/doesn't deserve to be mastered/carried to the extremes by great me"}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.76,0:07:00.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It goes against my sense of beauty. {/It would ruin my perfect aesthetics/opposes/goes against - unsure what he means by aesthetics here}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.88,0:07:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, right!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.04,0:07:04.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Sumo is a sports for fatasses!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.30,0:07:07.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Even you say smart things \Nevery once in a while! {/harako says good things too}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.64,0:07:16.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you make fun of sumo!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.52,0:07:20.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Sumo has always been \NJapan's trademark sport. {/national sport}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.19,0:07:24.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Moreover, it is rooted in a tradition \Nthat had persisted with us since ancient times. {/history dates back all the way to ancient time; age of the gods}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.09,0:07:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(0,200)} It was 2500 years ago in India, when the original Buddha \Nwon a beautiful princess as his wife in a sumo bout. {Buddha; Shakyamuni; the historical Buddha (5th c. BCE?)​/siddharta gautama; as for the story, I can only find some book titled "Buddha's bride and sumo - the origin of Japanese martial arts-literature novel" but no actual text or proof to this, only "Siddhartha and Yasodhara are cousins. Yashodhara's father was the brother of Queen Maya and Mahapajapati Gotami, while her mother Amita was the sister of King Suddhodana. Yashodhara married Siddhartha at the age of sixteen and the two shared a mutual respect and bond." - would assume it's a common misconception or a local meme}
Dialogue: 1,0:07:30.16,0:07:32.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(200,200)} Sumo is by no means superficial! {profound; deep}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.45,0:07:36.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(200,200)} Sumo is the most strenuous one \Nof all the known martial arts! {actually just "the strongest" but a sport can't be strong, right?}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.45,0:07:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(200,200)} If you lose a sumo bout, \Nyou lose your masculinity{/virility} along with it! {/by losing in sumo, you lose as a man - my ver is liberal, but is also more comedic/grotesque/blown out of proportion imo, plus it sits well with the next line}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.21,0:07:45.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(200,00)} If you can't win in sumo, \Nyou will never be able to make your woman happy! {/can't become happy with the woman you love}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.46,0:07:50.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I never had any idea! {/it was this way}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.22,0:07:53.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Sumo was actually \Nsuch a noble sport all this time!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.72,0:07:58.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Who's the blockhead now?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.43,0:08:03.81,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you like it when even the teacher says that \Nsumo's the most strenuous and the manliest of martial arts? {/virile}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.81,0:08:07.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm already looking forward \Nto our match in ten days!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.11,0:08:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn you...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.86,0:08:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha... ra and ko... {guess, maybe meaningless but maybe act. something important, hadda koto? harako? TLC} {8:08: I'm not sure about this one.\NThis might be a gag that only the Japanese would understand.\NMy best guess is that it has something to do with the syllables of his name matching with the numbers on the phone in some way.}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.53,0:08:14.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Old man! \NI need a sumo champion this instant! {/find for me}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.66,0:08:16.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Arrange an emergency coach for me!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.49,0:08:17.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Harako!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.03,0:08:23.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Teacher, in order to undergo special sumo training, \NI would require you to grant me a few days' leave! {/I would have to skip school for some while}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.37,0:08:24.82,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.05,0:08:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Much obliged. {and now}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.39,0:08:40.39,Default,,0,0,0,,But I never allowed it, Harako-kun! {/wait a minute}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.34,0:08:45.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Young Master, we'll get you straight to this man. {/we picked you up on the way to him}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.85,0:08:48.11,Default,,0,0,0,,We need to hurry, Old Man! \NWe can't waste a single moment! {/not a moment to waste; there is no time to lose; cannot wait any longer}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.15,0:08:57.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Harako, you prick... \NNo way I'll let him seize this victory without a fight. {unsure what he means by "can't gain the loss/benefit from losing" most likely either "can't afford to lose to him" or "won't give him victory without putting up a fight."}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.49,0:09:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,If it comes to this, \NI'll undergo special sumo training, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.52,0:09:05.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Taru, let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.43,0:09:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, Honmaru!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.83,0:09:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.49,0:09:13.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Skipping school for ten days starting now \Nto undergo special sumo training?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.51,0:09:15.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.59,0:09:17.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Honmaru...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.51,0:09:22.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad! Losing a match in sumo \Nmeans losing your masculinity as well!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.06,0:09:26.94,Default,,0,0,0,,He who can't win a sumo bout \Nwill never be able to make his woman happy!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.56,0:09:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like you did with boxing before, \Nteach me how to do sumo!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.53,0:09:39.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad, I beg you too! Need your teaching! {/plea from me too}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.04,0:09:46.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Not a word more, Honmaru! \NNot less to be expected from a son of mine!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.16,0:09:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright! A secluded special training in the mountains! {to shut oneself in (e.g. one's room); to be confined in; to seclude oneself; to hide away; to stay inside (one's shell)​}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.20,0:09:51.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.88,0:09:53.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.80,0:09:56.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Time to become as strong as 100 people! {hope it's hyakuninriki - tremendous strength; strength of a hundred people}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.05,0:09:57.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Honmaru!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.02,0:10:00.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Seclusion in the mountains? Sounds fun. {secluding oneself in the mountains; undertaking ascetic practices at a mountain temple}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.14,0:10:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.35,0:10:07.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Sis!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.73,0:10:10.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Sister Ria...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.67,0:10:17.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though it's still the height of winter, \Nyour outfit is already that exposing? {/still in the winter, wearing/dressing up/looking with a somewhat baring/exposing skin look/appearance}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.46,0:10:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The young ladies of recent years are all like this... {chikagoro is lately; recently; nowadays and musume is daughter/girl (i.e. a young, unmarried woman) so I think it's just a fancy/dated way to say "kids these days, man..."}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.08,0:10:26.62,Default,,0,0,0,,That previous dress was growing old on me, \Nso I decided to try a new one for a change. {to get tired of; to tire of; to lose interest in; to grow weary of; to get fed up with; to get sick of; to become bored with}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.96,0:10:28.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Like it? {/what do you think}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.67,0:10:34.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Looks mighty becoming on you, sister Ria.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.18,0:10:35.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Ten out of ten. {/just perfect}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.67,0:10:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.97,0:10:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,That is very well said. {/very much so}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.43,0:10:49.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.75,0:10:51.93,Default,,0,0,0,,If we need a secluded mountain, Canada has... {deep in the mountains; mountain recesses}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.36,0:10:53.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Just a spot for that right here. {/how about this area}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.98,0:10:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,In Canada?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.32,0:10:57.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Should I get us there all together with magic? {/let's go there with magic, including the house}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.18,0:10:59.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.07,0:11:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,A special training \Nin the great Canadian wilderness! {/great outdoors/big nature}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.00,0:11:03.32,Default,,0,0,0,,How about that? {/good isn't it}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.93,0:11:04.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Sounds good. {/I guess so}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.73,0:11:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I've also been wanting to visit Canada \Nat least once since long ago. {unsure where mae kara and ichidou belong here}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.83,0:11:10.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Brilliant as always, sister Ria!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.11,0:11:11.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Sister, please do!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.97,0:11:22.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Taru, what's with that globe?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.41,0:11:26.85,Default,,0,0,0,,This - Hop-globe, you need but to point {with your finger }where you wanna go \Nand it hops you there. {地ぴゅん儀 - pyun is "whiz (e.g. projectile through air); swoosh; whoosh; whistling sound" so I guess there's no pun, just a word that sounds a bit close to the original; I hate this name, I couldn't come up even with a distantly comprehensive pun, like "point/index/finger/swooshing-globe} {would assume last part "ittai basho itteru"}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.52,0:11:30.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{it's "Hoge, hoge, gegege" in manga, marked as teleportation spell}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.04,0:12:14.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It really sent us all the way here! {/we really came here}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.44,0:12:19.65,Default,,0,0,0,,No doubt about it, we're in Canada.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.65,0:12:24.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(0,300)} Honmaru! Let's do a snowball fight, \Njust like the last time! {/like before}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.00,0:12:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not what we came here for! {/we've no time for this}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.78,0:12:28.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's so cold!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.74,0:12:30.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Taru, do something about it with magic!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.45,0:12:31.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.00,0:12:34.71,Default,,0,0,0,,While losing even to the cold, \Nyou can't expect to win in sumo! {/if you don't overcome cold, you think you'll ... sumo?}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.65,0:12:36.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.96,0:12:37.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Now!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.16,0:12:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{Let's start }The special practice!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.92,0:12:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Miracle Star! {from manga, makes no sense but no other way around}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.58,0:12:50.82,Default,,0,0,0,,What's that for?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.82,0:12:55.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Sister's Miracle Star changes things \Ninto whatever she has in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.10,0:12:58.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Looks becoming on you, Honmaru.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.90,0:13:02.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Do your best, Honmaru! {have a good day; take care; see you​ }
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.61,0:13:06.85,Default,,0,0,0,,By the time you're back, \NI'll be waiting with dinner!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.24,0:13:15.62,Default,,0,0,0,,First, you need to get used to being heavy \Nby running in the deep snow! {lit is "practice/train legs and loins" but I think he means this, by extension}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.62,0:13:17.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Fight, Honmaru!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.21,0:13:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So cold! At this rate, I'll freeze to death \Nbefore the special training is concluded!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.48,0:13:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow! Canadian snow!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.83,0:13:45.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Tsk. It's good to be Taru! \NHe can just play around casually. {/having fun}
